00:00:50,385 --> 00:00:53,719
narrator: many thrill-seekers find zip lines exhilarating.   

4
00:00:53,721 --> 00:00:55,988
but without the proper braking system,    

5
00:00:55,990 --> 00:00:58,524
they can quickly become terrifying.        

6
00:00:58,526 --> 00:01:02,328
magnetic brakes are hands-free and engage automatically.    

7
00:01:02,330 --> 00:01:03,996
so there's no need to panic.   

8
00:01:03,998 --> 00:01:06,399
just hang on, enjoy the ride,  

9
00:01:06,401 --> 00:01:09,101
and let the brake take care of the landing.    

10
00:01:11,339 --> 00:01:14,073
in early human history, zip lines were used       

11
00:01:14,075 --> 00:01:17,276
to transfer supplies across dangerous terrain.    

12
00:01:17,278 --> 00:01:19,812
today, zip lines are popular with tourists    

13
00:01:19,814 --> 00:01:23,349
and adrenaline junkies all over the world.       

14
00:01:23,351 --> 00:01:27,152
as the rider approaches     
the landing, the brake engages  

15
00:01:27,154 --> 00:01:31,023
using magnets that induce eddy currents instead of friction.  

16
00:01:31,025 --> 00:01:34,060
this creates enough drag to stop the ride.        

17
00:01:37,031 --> 00:01:40,299
to make a zip line brake, they start with a drum.     

18
00:01:40,301 --> 00:01:44,102
it's made of zinc-coated steel to prevent rust.         

19
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:47,740
a worker sends off the zinc so they can add the magnets.   

20
00:01:50,111 --> 00:01:53,980
he hammers locating pins into the metal.         

21
00:01:53,982 --> 00:01:56,582
he applies adhesive to the sanded areas,       

22
00:01:56,584 --> 00:02:00,786
then places magnets onto the adhesive.        

23
00:02:00,788 --> 00:02:04,456
he uses steel pins as a guide.  

24
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:08,227
as the adhesive cures,     
the magnets bond to the metal.  

25
00:02:10,331 --> 00:02:13,933
next, he applies a bonding agent to a shaft bearing        

26
00:02:13,935 --> 00:02:17,136
and inserts it into the hole in the center.   

27
00:02:17,138 --> 00:02:18,737
using a hydraulic press,     

28
00:02:18,739 --> 00:02:21,440
he drives the bearing further into the hole.      

29
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:26,812
these rotor arms will spin in the magnetic field              

30
00:02:26,814 --> 00:02:29,881
to create the braking force.   

31
00:02:29,883 --> 00:02:32,618
a worker fits gears into two plates         

32
00:02:32,620 --> 00:02:37,289
and bolts the plates to each side of the rotor assembly.            

33
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:40,159
he tests the rotor arms and slides the rotor gears    

34
00:02:40,161 --> 00:02:43,095
onto the shaft already installed in the brake drum.        

35
00:02:45,099 --> 00:02:48,166
he opens the rotors and spins them.         

36
00:02:48,168 --> 00:02:49,501
he adds a ring of magnets    

37
00:02:49,503 --> 00:02:53,505
to surround the rotors in a magnetic field.       

38
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:55,241
satisfied with the fit,     

39
00:02:55,243 --> 00:02:58,778
he removes the rotor assembly from the drum temporarily    

40
00:02:58,780 --> 00:03:01,646
and clips springs to the rotor.             

41
00:03:01,648 --> 00:03:05,984
these reaction springs will cushion the braking action.             

42
00:03:05,986 --> 00:03:10,856
now a worker reinstalls the rotor device in the brake drum.              

43
00:03:10,858 --> 00:03:13,993
he places the magnetic ring back on top.           

44
00:03:13,995 --> 00:03:17,296
the strong magnetic attraction secures it to the assembly.   

45
00:03:20,067 --> 00:03:24,670
the next part is a large ring with more gears inside it.    

46
00:03:24,672 --> 00:03:27,239
he hammers and then screws it in place.   

47
00:03:30,011 --> 00:03:33,579
he spins the assembly again to confirm it's functional.   

48
00:03:36,951 --> 00:03:40,752
he installs the final two gears on the end of the shaft.     

49
00:03:40,754 --> 00:03:44,690
this completes the core of the zip line brake.      

50
00:03:44,692 --> 00:03:47,693
another employee stitches a nylon hand grip    

51
00:03:47,695 --> 00:03:49,829
to tough, synthetic webbing.   

52
00:03:49,831 --> 00:03:53,165
when this webbing is pulled out of the brake,   

53
00:03:53,167 --> 00:03:55,034
it will set the rotor arms in motion     

54
00:03:55,036 --> 00:03:57,937
to create the eddy currents that are the braking force.   

55
00:04:00,174 --> 00:04:02,842
after protecting the brake core with a metal plate,       

56
00:04:02,844 --> 00:04:07,112
a worker puts the unit in a plastic case.        

57
00:04:07,114 --> 00:04:10,449
he installs a plate on the shaft for the webbing to sit on,    

58
00:04:10,451 --> 00:04:12,584
then loops the webbing around it.            

59
00:04:12,586 --> 00:04:16,455
he also places a drum on top for the retraction spring.    

60
00:04:16,457 --> 00:04:19,457
he applies silicone adhesive around the drum.         

61
00:04:19,459 --> 00:04:22,194
this secures the aluminum base plate.     

62
00:04:22,196 --> 00:04:25,197
he now inserts the retraction spring.      

63
00:04:25,199 --> 00:04:28,000
he caps the spring with a metal plate        

64
00:04:28,002 --> 00:04:30,869
and reinforces the clips with metallic tape.       

65
00:04:30,871 --> 00:04:35,607
using a crank, he winds more  
of the webbing into the brake.  

66
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:37,476
he tightens the metal shackle  

67
00:04:37,478 --> 00:04:40,479
that holds the two sections of webbing together       

68
00:04:40,481 --> 00:04:43,082
and winds the rest of it into the device.         

69
00:04:45,953 --> 00:04:48,087
he inserts a guide roller for the webbing         

70
00:04:48,089 --> 00:04:50,322
and adds a two-part retaining clip.         

71
00:04:54,829 --> 00:04:57,730
he secures the clip with a rounded metal pin.    

72
00:04:59,901 --> 00:05:04,770
this next part is a plastic insert for the top of the case.              

73
00:05:04,772 --> 00:05:09,041
he screws a nut onto the shaft to lock down the insert.     

74
00:05:09,043 --> 00:05:12,178
he places the top half of the case onto the brake assembly            

75
00:05:12,180 --> 00:05:16,048
and secures it to the lower half.        

76
00:05:16,050 --> 00:05:19,985
he snaps a dust cover onto the case.          

77
00:05:19,987 --> 00:05:23,856
they're now ready to test this zip line brake system.   

78
00:05:23,858 --> 00:05:25,791
a motor pulls out the webbing  

79
00:05:25,793 --> 00:05:27,593
to simulate different body weights           

80
00:05:27,595 --> 00:05:29,728
and different zip lining speeds,             

81
00:05:29,730 --> 00:05:34,800
while a computer analyzes the brake's performance.     

82
00:05:34,802 --> 00:05:36,868
with magnetic zip line brakes,  

83
00:05:36,870 --> 00:05:39,738
riders can come down at a wide range of speeds    

84
00:05:39,740 --> 00:05:42,340
but still slow down at the same rate,        

85
00:05:42,342 --> 00:05:46,178
ensuring that everyone has a fun but safe ride.     

