00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:16,500
so after cutting a part for the right shoe,    

251
00:17:16,502 --> 00:17:20,438
he flips it over and cuts the same part for the left shoe.              

252
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,707
they stencil on guide marks for stitching    

253
00:17:22,709 --> 00:17:25,309
and stamp on a production number.       

254
00:17:25,311 --> 00:17:28,513
due to the natural variations between hides,          

255
00:17:28,515 --> 00:17:30,315
they cut parts for a pair of shoes       

256
00:17:30,317 --> 00:17:32,784
from the same piece of leather.            

257
00:17:32,786 --> 00:17:34,719
a production number keeps the parts         

258
00:17:34,721 --> 00:17:39,190
from being inadvertently used on a different pair of shoes.  

259
00:17:39,192 --> 00:17:41,526
they place the part under a template         

260
00:17:41,528 --> 00:17:43,728
and run it through a lateral knife.         

261
00:17:43,730 --> 00:17:47,999
this thins the leather where it will overlap adjoining parts              

262
00:17:48,001 --> 00:17:52,003
so the thickness of the upper shoe is uniform throughout.   

263
00:17:52,005 --> 00:17:54,205
they apply reinforcement fabric             

264
00:17:54,207 --> 00:17:57,141
to the most wear-prone areas of the shoe.           

265
00:17:57,143 --> 00:18:00,544
this machine bonds these adhesive factory enforcements  

266
00:18:00,546 --> 00:18:02,814
with pressure and heat.     

267
00:18:02,816 --> 00:18:05,283
now sewers begin assembling the upper.      

268
00:18:05,285 --> 00:18:07,552
they glue the parts for the lining together     

269
00:18:07,554 --> 00:18:10,154
because stitches that are on the inside of the shoe    

270
00:18:10,156 --> 00:18:12,690
can sometimes irritate the foot.              

271
00:18:12,692 --> 00:18:15,426
the lining is made of soft calf leather,      

272
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:18,696
except for a small piece of rougher goat leather at the back              

273
00:18:18,698 --> 00:18:20,065
to grip the heel.        

274
00:18:22,769 --> 00:18:26,638
they sew in the lining one section at a time.      

275
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:31,442
this is the rear section of the upper, called the heel cap.              

276
00:18:31,444 --> 00:18:33,244
after sewing one side,      

277
00:18:33,246 --> 00:18:36,981
they insert a foam padding to cushion the back of the foot.              

278
00:18:36,983 --> 00:18:40,585
then they fold the lining over to encase the padding.      

279
00:18:45,192 --> 00:18:49,160
this machine punches holes and 
embeds eyelets into the upper.  

280
00:18:53,066 --> 00:18:56,668
then a sewer attaches two more parts of the upper,   

281
00:18:56,670 --> 00:18:58,470
the tongue and the vamp.     

282
00:19:02,208 --> 00:19:06,177
another sewer finishes the upper             
by stitching on the vamp ring.  

283
00:19:11,217 --> 00:19:14,619
they put the upper into a mold on a forming machine.      

284
00:19:14,621 --> 00:19:18,356
the machine works like an iron, applying both heat and pressure            

285
00:19:18,358 --> 00:19:21,726
to form the heel cap into the perfect shape.     

286
00:19:23,696 --> 00:19:26,764
the next forming machine uses the same process      

287
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:28,833
to round the toe cap.      

288
00:19:38,178 --> 00:19:41,279
now a sewer stitches a hole to the upper.          

289
00:19:45,451 --> 00:19:48,720
then they steam the upper and insert a last.        

290
00:19:48,722 --> 00:19:51,256
a last is a foot-shaped plastic form           

291
00:19:51,258 --> 00:19:54,926
that matches the specific shape and size of the shoe.      

292
00:19:54,928 --> 00:19:57,996
they place the upper into a heat setter.       

293
00:19:57,998 --> 00:20:01,465
the heat forms the upper to the shape of the last.    

294
00:20:01,467 --> 00:20:02,934
they roll out wrinkles      

295
00:20:02,936 --> 00:20:05,837
and flatten any bulges with heat and pressure.     

296
00:20:08,141 --> 00:20:09,407
they place the upper       

297
00:20:09,409 --> 00:20:11,543
in a template of the shoe's outer sole     

298
00:20:11,545 --> 00:20:13,211
and trace the top.        

299
00:20:13,213 --> 00:20:15,747
they grind the leather below that line.         

300
00:20:15,749 --> 00:20:19,217
this roughens the surface to help with adhesion.      

301
00:20:19,219 --> 00:20:21,085
they apply heat-activated glue  

302
00:20:21,087 --> 00:20:23,220
to the roughened area and the sole,          

303
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:27,024
which is made of molded polyurethane.     

304
00:20:27,026 --> 00:20:29,026
they let the glue dry.      

305
00:20:29,028 --> 00:20:31,229
then they activate the glue with a heater          

306
00:20:31,231 --> 00:20:34,265
and join the upper and sole.   

307
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:37,034
they place the shoe in a vacuum press.        

308
00:20:37,036 --> 00:20:38,837
the press sucks out the air   

309
00:20:38,839 --> 00:20:42,507
while drawing the upper and sole tightly together.        

310
00:20:42,509 --> 00:20:46,711
next, they add an anatomically shaped footbed insole.      

311
00:20:46,713 --> 00:20:49,180
it's made of a moisture absorbing combination      

312
00:20:49,182 --> 00:20:53,584
of cork and latex with leather on top.       

313
00:20:53,586 --> 00:20:56,187
then they lace the shoes     

314
00:20:56,189 --> 00:21:00,125
and insert cardboard to support the shape during transport.   

315
00:21:02,195 --> 00:21:04,728
they spray the upper with a chemical solution     

316
00:21:04,730 --> 00:21:07,098
that makes the leather water-resistant.         

317
00:21:10,136 --> 00:21:14,005
the second set of insoles goes in the shoe box.      

318
00:21:14,007 --> 00:21:16,274
these shoes are designed with enough room         

319
00:21:16,276 --> 00:21:19,177
to insert a custom orthotic device, if needed.   

